A bug report option has been added to the Twine section.

I have some people to thank for this.

Firstly: Thanks to JakdragonX for getting me back on course with his critique. He made me realize that I had lost the theme of mystery in my earlier drafts.

Secondly: Thanks to Doctor Fullham for inspiring me to do the stupid, stupid thing you'll find at the last offset.

Thirdly: Thanks to Dr Balthazaar for helping me with this. They had no creative input whatsoever, they just helped me with formatting when I had my hand gimped from a car accident.

Fourthly: Thanks to Captain Kirby for telling me to reign in my ambition on this.

Fifthly: I have to thank Kyza for helping me get the freakin' hover elements to work.

Lastly: thank you to everyone who agreed to 'die' in the name of this stupid, stupid meta idea.

Actually last but certainly not least: glewmie was a massive help in helping me learn the basics of Twine. So thanks to them for that.

The Twine file still might have some bugs in it if you run into an infinite loop or an error message while it's trying to execute, PM me and I'll get it fixed ASAP.

